<subSubSection id="C323654CCA1E5339FC82CC2C2F770B7D" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8636C7CA1E5339FC82CC2C2F770B7D" blockId="11.[749,1404,117,1118]" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FC82CC2C28190D13" box="[773,1070,539,560]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FC82CC2C2F6B0D13" bold="true" box="[773,860,539,560]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">Notes—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FCDBCC2C28190D13" authorityName="Vorontsova &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Kirika &amp; Muthoka" authorityYear="2010" box="[860,1070,539,560]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="malindiense">Solanum malindiense</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has undulate leaves of consistent shape, long-acuminate calyx lobes, curved prickles covering the calyx from late bud onwards, and a pubescent ovary with stellate trichomes persisting until the developing fruit reaches 1 cm in diameter. 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FB86CCA728E50D86" authorityName="Vorontsova &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Kirika &amp; Muthoka" authorityYear="2010" box="[1025,1234,656,677]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="malindiense">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FB86CCA728E50D86" box="[1025,1234,656,677]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">Solanum malindiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the northern continuation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FC11CC9928170DE0" baseAuthorityName="Dammer" box="[918,1056,686,707]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solano" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="usaramense">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FC11CC9928170DE0" box="[918,1056,686,707]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">S. usaramense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
populations in the coastal areas of Mozambique, Tanzania, and southern Kenya, with wider and more lobed leaves, larger yellow berries, and sparse indumentum. The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FC42CD3229260C38" authority="Dammer" authorityName="Dammer" box="[965,1297,773,795]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monotanthum">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FC42CD32289B0C39" box="[965,1196,773,794]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">Solanum monotanthum</emphasis>
Dammer
</taxonomicName>
has been erroneously applied to populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FB0DCD14296E0C1A" box="[1162,1369,803,825]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="usaramense">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FB0DCD14296E0C1A" box="[1162,1369,803,825]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">Solanum usaramense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in coastal Kenya and Tanzania. Type material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FB54CD7629420C76" box="[1235,1397,832,854]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monotanthum">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FB54CD7629420C76" box="[1235,1397,832,854]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">S. monotanthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in Universität Göttingen suggests the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FA9CCD692F760CB3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monotanthum">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FA9CCD692F760CB3" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">S. monotanthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is actually a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FBD2CD4C29190CB2" authority="Vatke" authorityName="Vatke" box="[1109,1326,891,913]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zanzibarense">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FBD2CD4C28DC0CB3" box="[1109,1259,891,912]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">S. zanzibarense</emphasis>
Vatke
</taxonomicName>
and is not synonymous with either 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FBADCDAE28800C8D" box="[1066,1207,921,942]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="usaramense">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FBADCDAE28800C8D" box="[1066,1207,921,942]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">S. usaramense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FB58CDAE29580C8E" authorityName="Vorontsova &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Kirika &amp; Muthoka" authorityYear="2010" box="[1247,1391,920,942]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="malindiense">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FB58CDAE29580C8E" box="[1247,1391,920,942]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">S. malindiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The habit and yellowish regularly undulate leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FAA8CD812F0A0CCB" authorityName="Vorontsova &amp; Christenhusz &amp; Kirika &amp; Muthoka" authorityYear="2010" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="malindiense">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FAA8CD812F0A0CCB" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">S. malindiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are reminiscent of two other species of East African coasts: the sympatric 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FC5CCDC628440B26" box="[987,1139,1008,1030]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zanzibarense">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FC5CCDC628440B26" box="[987,1139,1008,1030]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">S. zanzibarense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D44CA1E5339FB28CDC62F1B0B00" authority="A. E. Gonc." authorityName="A. E. Gonc." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="11" pageNumber="905" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="litoraneum">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD5CA1E5339FB28CDC629010B26" box="[1199,1334,1008,1030]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="905">S. litoraneum</emphasis>
A. E. Gonç.
</taxonomicName>
from coastal Mozambique and Tanzania, although the corollas, anthers and fruit are larger than in either of these species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
